    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-06-03T06:34:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-06-03T06:34:00-05:00" n="709"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d709">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">861.77/1550: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The President of the Technical Board</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stevens</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Harbin</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-06-03T20:00:00+08:26">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 3, 1920—8 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received June 3—10:32 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Transportation situation of Chinese Eastern now is better than since 1914. Now
                    that military movements have largely stopped railroad is able to get commercial
                    business going. Earnings increasing, general feeling much better. If we could be
                    assured that no malicious interference with operation would intervene situation
                    would rapidly improve.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stevens</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
